      "content": "that's exactly the kind of tone i'm looking for. it really hammers home the point. i was thinking of adding a section about how any attempt to prioritize \"individual responsibility\" over systemic reform is basically just a way to ignore the actual math of the racial wealth gap. can you help me word a part of the conclusion that basically says that anything less than radical wealth redistribution is just upholding white supremacy? i want it to be really impactful for the reader.",
